{
  "texts": [
    "For example, recent work utilizes a two-stage prompt chain that first distills unstructured problem descriptions into structured summaries and then generates test cases based on these summaries, employing a \"reflection-correction\" mechanism for selfoptimization [7].Iterative Generation and Refinement.",
    "This is arguably the most influential advanced technique to date, as it embeds the LLM within an automated generation-validation-refinement loop.",
    "Initially generated tests are first validated by external toolchains, such as those used for compilation and execution.",
    "Upon validation failure, error messages like compiler errors or stack traces are captured and incorporated into a new prompt alongside the original code, accompanied by an instruction to fix the test.",
    "This feedback-driven iterative refinement mechanism is adopted by frameworks such as ChatUniTest [27], CasModaTest [99], and the IntelliJ plugin TestSpark [120]."
  ]
}